msgid "ValveOperation"
msgstr "ValveOperation"

msgid "ValveOperation_DROPWEIGHT"
msgstr "The method of valve operation where:[[DROPWEIGHT]]: A valve that is closed by the action of a weighted lever being released"

msgid "ValveOperation_FLOAT"
msgstr "the closure normally being made by the action of heat on a fusible link in the wire
[[FLOAT]]: A valve that is opened and closed by the action of a float that rises and falls with water level"

msgid "ValveOperation_HYDRAULIC"
msgstr "The float may be a ball attached to a lever or other mechanism
[[HYDRAULIC]]: A valve that is opened and closed by hydraulic actuation
[[LEVER]]: A valve that is opened and closed by the action of a lever rotating the gate within the valve"

msgid "ValveOperation_LEVER"
msgstr "The method of valve operation where:[[DROPWEIGHT]]: A valve that is closed by the action of a weighted lever being released"

msgid "ValveOperation_LOCKSHIELD"
msgstr "[[LOCKSHIELD]]: A valve that requires the use of a special lockshield key for opening and closing"

msgid "ValveOperation_MOTORIZED"
msgstr "[[MOTORIZED]]: A valve that is opened and closed by the action of an electric motor on an actuator
[[PNEUMATIC]]: A valve that is opened and closed by pneumatic actuation
[[SOLENOID]]: A valve that is normally held open by a magnetic field in a coil acting on the gate but that is closed immediately if the electrical current generating the magnetic field is removed"

msgid "ValveOperation_PNEUMATIC"
msgstr "[[MOTORIZED]]: A valve that is opened and closed by the action of an electric motor on an actuator
[[PNEUMATIC]]: A valve that is opened and closed by pneumatic actuation
[[SOLENOID]]: A valve that is normally held open by a magnetic field in a coil acting on the gate but that is closed immediately if the electrical current generating the magnetic field is removed"

msgid "ValveOperation_SOLENOID"
msgstr "[[MOTORIZED]]: A valve that is opened and closed by the action of an electric motor on an actuator
[[PNEUMATIC]]: A valve that is opened and closed by pneumatic actuation
[[SOLENOID]]: A valve that is normally held open by a magnetic field in a coil acting on the gate but that is closed immediately if the electrical current generating the magnetic field is removed"

msgid "ValveOperation_SPRING"
msgstr "[[SPRING]]: A valve that is normally held in position by the pressure of a spring on a plate but that may be caused to open if the pressure of the fluid is sufficient to overcome the spring pressure"

msgid "ValveOperation_THERMOSTATIC"
msgstr "[[THERMOSTATIC]]: A valve in which the ports are opened or closed to maintain a required predetermined temperature"

msgid "ValveOperation_WHEEL"
msgstr "[[WHEEL]]: A valve that is opened and closed by the action of a wheel moving the gate within the valve"

msgid "ValveOperation_OTHER"
msgstr "The float may be a ball attached to a lever or other mechanism
[[HYDRAULIC]]: A valve that is opened and closed by hydraulic actuation
[[LEVER]]: A valve that is opened and closed by the action of a lever rotating the gate within the valve"

msgid "ValveOperation_NOTKNOWN"
msgstr "[[NOTKNOWN]]"

msgid "ValveOperation_UNSET"
msgstr "[[UNSET]]"

msgid "ValveMechanism"
msgstr "ValveMechanism"

msgid "ValveMechanism_BALL"
msgstr "The mechanism by which the valve function is achieved where:[[BALL]]: Valve that has a ported ball that can be turned relative to the body seat ports"

msgid "ValveMechanism_BUTTERFLY"
msgstr "[[BUTTERFLY]]: Valve in which a streamlined disc pivots about a diametric axis"

msgid "ValveMechanism_CONFIGUREDGATE"
msgstr "[[CONFIGUREDGATE]]: Screwdown valve in which the closing gate is shaped in a configured manner to have a more precise control of pressure and flow change across the valve"

msgid "ValveMechanism_GLAND"
msgstr "[[GLAND]]: Valve with a tapered seating"

msgid "ValveMechanism_GLOBE"
msgstr "[[GLOBE]]: Screwdown valve that has a spherical body"

msgid "ValveMechanism_LUBRICATEDPLUG"
msgstr "[[LUBRICATEDPLUG]]: Plug valve in which a lubricant is injected under pressure between the plug face and the body"

msgid "ValveMechanism_NEEDLE"
msgstr "[[NEEDLE]]: Valve for regulating the flow in or from a pipe"

msgid "ValveMechanism_PARALLELSLIDE"
msgstr "[[PARALLELSLIDE]]: Screwdown valve that has a machined plate that slides in formed grooves to form a seal"

msgid "ValveMechanism_PLUG"
msgstr "in which a rotatable plug is retained by means of a gland and gland packing"

msgid "ValveMechanism_WEDGEGATE"
msgstr "[[WEDGEGATE]]: Screwdown valve that has a wedge shaped plate fitting into tapered guides to form a seal"

